    • setCell

      public void setCell​(int row, int col, int val) throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
      Specified by:
      setCell in interface SudokuSolver
      Parameters:
      row - must be between 1-9 since the sudokuboard is 9x9
      col - must be between 1-9 since the sudokuboard is 9x9
      val - must be between 1-9 (following the rules of sudoku) or 0 if cell should be marked as unsolved.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any of the parameters are out of range or the if val can't be placed at the current cell.
